[thinking] **Analyzing Graal static analysis**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m realizing that Graal static analysis might not be able to identify System properties. When it comes to native images, it seems that using Class.forName for classes included in the image often works to get the Class object. However, reflective instantiation requires registration. I think Constructor.newInstance needs reflection configuration, and I'm curious whether the agent collects data during native metadata generation. It's puzzling that user-code-filter might exclude test classes, yet the agent could be generating test-only metadata that isn’t filtered. I really need to understand that filter better!
